<subSubSection pageId="302" pageNumber="303" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="302.[136,778,1465,2070]" lastBlockId="302.[810,1452,173,335]" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,298,1636,1662]" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars, G. O." box="[329,476,1636,1662]" journalOrPublisher="Monstrilloida and Notodelphyoida, Bergen" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" pagination="1 - 91" refId="ref330626" refString="Sars, G. O. (1921) An account of the Crustacea of Norway with short descriptions and figures of all the species, Vol. 8. Copepoda. Monstrilloida and Notodelphyoida, Bergen, pp. 1 - 91, pls. 1 - 37." title="An account of the Crustacea of Norway with short descriptions and figures of all the species, Vol. 8. Copepoda" type="book chapter" year="1921">Sars (1921)</bibRefCitation>
established this genus to accommodate 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[344,467,1669,1695]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thorelli">
<emphasis box="[344,467,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">D. thorelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of “several peculiarities, both as regards the outward appearance of the body and the structure of some of the appendages”. Unfortunately, Sars did not specify the nature of the peculiarities which he regarded as of generic significance although the unsegmented condition of the mandibular exopod is diagnostic. 
<bibRefCitation author="Illg" box="[383,504,1873,1900]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg (1958)</bibRefCitation>
explored the distinction between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1921" box="[246,387,1908,1934]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[246,387,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">Doropygella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1859" box="[459,582,1908,1933]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,582,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">Doropygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recognized a lineage he referred to as “the 
<emphasis box="[519,705,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">thorelli-normani</emphasis>
line”, which he considered represented a natural grouping. As a consequence, 
<bibRefCitation author="Illg" box="[314,435,2009,2036]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg (1958)</bibRefCitation>
transferred three species from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1859" box="[136,259,2044,2069]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,259,2044,2069]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">Doropygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1921" box="[305,445,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[305,445,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">Doropygella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brady, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Brady" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[465,773,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="normani">
<emphasis box="[465,599,2044,2069]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">D. normani</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brady, G. S." bookContentInfo="148 pp" box="[618,764,2044,2070]" journalOrPublisher="The Ray Society, London" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref327314" refString="Brady, G. S. (1878) A monograph of the free and semi-parasitic Copepoda of the British islands. Vol. 1. The Ray Society, London, 148 pp, pls 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 58691" title="A monograph of the free and semi-parasitic Copepoda of the British islands. Vol. 1" type="book chapter" year="1878">Brady, 1878</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brady, 1878)" baseAuthorityName="Brady" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[810,1152,173,199]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porcicauda">
<emphasis box="[810,977,173,199]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">D. porcicauda</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brady, G. S." bookContentInfo="148 pp" box="[996,1143,173,199]" journalOrPublisher="The Ray Society, London" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref327314" refString="Brady, G. S. (1878) A monograph of the free and semi-parasitic Copepoda of the British islands. Vol. 1. The Ray Society, London, 148 pp, pls 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 58691" title="A monograph of the free and semi-parasitic Copepoda of the British islands. Vol. 1" type="book chapter" year="1878">Brady, 1878</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thorell, 1859)" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1859" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psyllus">
<emphasis box="[1222,1340,173,199]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">D. psyllus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell, T." journalOrPublisher="Kongliga Svenska vetenskapsakademiens handlingar" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" pagination="1 - 84" part="3" refId="ref331272" refString="Thorell, T. (1859) Bidrag til Kannedomen om Krustaceer som lefva i arter af Slagtet Ascidia L. Kongliga Svenska vetenskapsakademiens handlingar, 3 (8), 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 58671" title="Bidrag til Kannedomen om Krustaceer som lefva i arter af Slagtet Ascidia L" type="journal article" year="1859">Thorell, 1859</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Two new species have been added subseqently, 
<taxonomicName authority="Monniot, C., 1981" authorityName="Monniot, C." authorityYear="1981" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hastalae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">D. hastalae</emphasis>
Monniot, C., 1981
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Monniot, C., 1961" authorityName="Monniot, C." authorityYear="1961" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doropygopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="302" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinicauda">
<emphasis box="[1180,1339,241,267]" italics="true" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">D. spinicauda</emphasis>
Monniot, C., 1961
</taxonomicName>
.Afurther two new species are described here and the 
<typeStatus box="[851,899,309,335]" pageId="302" pageNumber="303">type</typeStatus>
species is redescribed based on new material.
</paragraph>
